      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "One thousand dollars Is the esti-\nmated damage resulting from the fire\nwhich ravaged the shed occupied by\nthe Spokane Mattress factory on the\nbig island yesterday afternoon.\n\n\nThe fire started about 4 o'clock and\nfor a time threatened to destroy the\nmain building. A strong wind was\nblowing and the firemen had all they\ncould do to save the larger structure\nChief Myers of the fire department\nstated that in his opinion the damage\nwould easily reach $1,000. II. ]. Car\nman, one of the owners Of the fac\ntory, stated that the machinery alone\nwould amount to a considerable loss\nfor there were three machines valued\nat $500 each in the building. The\nshed was owned by the Washington\nWater Power company."
    }
